# Unplugging — Project Context

This is a marketing website for **Edward Worbis**, a life coach specializing in **technology and gaming addiction recovery**.

## Terminology

- Use **life coach** — never **counselor**
- Use **counseling** — never **life coaching**
- Title: **Technology & Gaming Addiction Life Coach**

## Voice

- Site copy uses first person ("I", "me", "my") — never refer to Edward in the third person
- Exception: the site logo and page `<title>` tags may use "Edward Worbis"
- No copyright notices anywhere on the site

## Primary Goal

Promote counseling services and convert visitors into contacts. Every page, design choice, and piece of copy should support that goal.

## Audience

People (or their loved ones) struggling with unhealthy screen time, gaming, or digital habits who are looking for professional help.

## Site Structure

- **Home** (`index.html`) — hero, value proposition, primary call to action
- **Challenges** (`challenges.html`) — common struggles clients face
- **FAQ** (`faq.html`) — answers objections and builds trust
- **Get In Touch** (`get-in-touch.html`) — main conversion page; prioritize clear, low-friction contact paths

## Content & Design Principles

- Tone: calm, conversational, and professional — not preachy, alarmist, or sales-driven
- Emphasize that help is available and not every path looks the same
- Guide visitors toward getting in touch; CTAs should be visible and compelling
- Avoid language that stigmatizes addiction, shames visitors, or overpromises

## Tech Stack

Static HTML pages styled with SCSS (`src/scss/`), built with Vite.
